<h1>About</h1>
<p>
  This page is build on <strong>Ruby on Rails</strong>, changes made to the 
  project can be tracked at project's <strong><%= link_to 'GitHub page', 
  "https://github.com/smilzy/Twittie", target: "_blank" %></strong>.
</p>
<p>
  This app is a copy of a popular blogging app Twitter, made with help of
  <strong><%= link_to  "Learn Web Development with Rails", "https://railstutorial.org",
  target: "_blank" %> </strong> with some tweaks. Users can post short messages 
  on their dashboards. Next thing to add is following users (in progress).
</p>
<p>
  Front is built using <strong>Bootstrap, CSS3 / SASS</strong>, project uses
  test-driven development, full user authentication made from scratch.
</p>
<p>
  Application uses <strong>Capistrano</strong> for deployment to live servers
  @MyDevil, with mailer setup on the server, and domain at a different service.
</p>
<p>
  Feel free to check out first project of mine at <strong><%= link_to "Heroku", 
  "https://stormy-earth-37856.herokuapp.com", target: "_blank" %></strong>.
  It supports <strong>e-commerce</strong> functionality, users can register
  for free or pay a monthly fee and automatically get billed in order to see
  additional contact information of other users.
</p>
